<br>
Anyways, this could be a really fun skill, heck I still think it's cool if not all that useful.<br>
<br>
First off they need to fix the issue with commands being given to multiple pets. Easiest and ideal way I suppose would be making pet commands broadcast to all your active pets.<br>
<br>
Next problem is heals and buffs. You can't target the host or servant pets with heals or buffs, the autotarget thingy causes you to target your normal pet. Worse, the heals and buffs don't land even on your normal pet. So while using these skills, you lose control of your pets, and you can neither heal nor buff them. I can deal with not being able to heal or buff for the duration I guess, but losing commands is pretty bad.<br>
<br>
Dunno why they made this a bolt, really ought to be a DD. I'm assuming the pets are green so that people can't just kill them for xp. If they can't find some way to make these pets closer in level to the caster and avoid this exploit, then the spell on the drake really needs to be made nigh unresistable or it's just not gonna land on anything significant.<br>
<br>
It should also always cast, never melee. I don't know if that is possible, but I can see this skill being made useless on PvP servers by someone just running up next to it so it melees instead of casts. And on all servers, let's face it, we got this pet to cast stuff, not take little swipes at mobs.<br>
<br>
The servant was a very, very cool idea. And really just needs a bit of tweaking for it to be great.<br>
<br>
Kinelaria<br>
Taeru<br>
